## Feature

Only allow one extension detail tab open at a time. When the user opens a second extension, it should replace the existing extension tab rather than opening a new tab alongside it.

### Current behavior

**File:** \`apps/orchestrator-web/src/routes/editor/index.tsx\` (~lines 831-862)

\`handleExtensionClick\` currently:
1. Checks if the SAME extension is already open â†’ activates it
2. Otherwise, creates a new tab and appends it: \`setTabs(prev => [...prev, newTab])\`

This means opening Extension A then Extension B results in two tabs.

### Desired behavior

Opening Extension B when Extension A's tab is already open should:
1. Replace Extension A's tab with Extension B's tab (same position in tab bar)
2. Activate the new tab

### Implementation

Modify \`handleExtensionClick\` (~line 832) to find and replace any existing extension tab:

\`\`\`typescript
const handleExtensionClick = useCallback((ext: OpenVSXExtensionSummary) => {
  const tabId = \`ext:\${ext.namespace}.\${ext.name}\`;
  const displayName = ext.displayName || ext.name;

  // Check if this exact extension is already open
  const existing = tabsRef.current.find(t => t.id === tabId);
  if (existing) {
    setActiveTabId(tabId);
    return;
  }

  captureEditorContent();

  const newTab: EditorTab = {
    id: tabId,
    name: displayName,
    path: \`Extension: \${displayName}\`,
    content: '',
    savedContent: '',
    language: 'plaintext',
    source: 'extension',
    isPreview: false,
    isDirty: false,
    hasUnsavedChanges: false,
    savedVersionId: 0,
    extensionId: \`\${ext.namespace}.\${ext.name}\`,
  };

  setTabs(prev => {
    // Find an existing extension tab to replace
    const existingExtIndex = prev.findIndex(t => t.source === 'extension');
    if (existingExtIndex !== -1) {
      // Replace the existing extension tab in-place
      const updated = [...prev];
      updated[existingExtIndex] = newTab;
      return updated;
    }
    // No existing extension tab â€” add as new
    return [...prev, newTab];
  });
  setActiveTabId(tabId);
}, [captureEditorContent]);
\`\`\`

Key points:
- Finds ANY tab with \`source === 'extension'\` (not just matching ID)
- Replaces it in the same position in the tab array (preserves tab order)
- If no extension tab exists, appends as before
- The check for \`existing\` (same extension already open) stays as the first guard

### Edge cases

- **Extension tab has no unsaved changes** (extensions are read-only detail pages), so no save prompt is needed when replacing
- **If the replaced extension tab was the active tab**, the new tab becomes active (which it does since \`setActiveTabId(tabId)\` is called)
- **If the replaced extension tab was NOT active**, the new tab still becomes active (same behavior as clicking any extension)

## Files to change

