## Summary
Fix a bug where stale SSE output data permanently blocks the fresher polling fallback data from being displayed on agent cards.

## Root Cause
In `apps/orchestrator-web/src/components/activity/ActiveAgentsDashboard.tsx:130-143`:
```typescript
const sseOutput = outputByAgent.get(agent.id);
let effectiveOutput = sseOutput;
if (!effectiveOutput) {
  const persisted = latestBySession[session.id];
  // ...
}
```

SSE output always takes priority over polling. Once `outputByAgent` has an entry for an agent (set before SSE processing breaks), the 2-second polling data in `latestBySession` is never used â€” even when the polling data is minutes fresher.

This means pre-existing agents (which got SSE entries before the 100-event cap was hit) show permanently stale data, while new agents (with no SSE entry) correctly fall back to polling.

## Fix Approach
Add timestamp comparison when choosing between SSE and polling data. Use the fresher of the two:
```typescript
const sseOutput = outputByAgent.get(agent.id);
const persisted = latestBySession[session.id];
// Use whichever is more recent
let effectiveOutput: AgentOutput | undefined;
if (sseOutput && persisted) {
  effectiveOutput = new Date(sseOutput.timestamp) >= new Date(persisted.timestamp)
    ? sseOutput
    : { content: persisted.content, timestamp: persisted.timestamp, eventType: persisted.type };
} else {
  effectiveOutput = sseOutput ?? (persisted ? { ... } : undefined);
}
```

